Created files:
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Dispatch/MainThreadDispatchQueue.cs
    Pure C# main-thread dispatch queue. Holds two independent shared
    structures: ConcurrentDictionary<string, MessageEnvelope> _stateSlots
    (per-topic state slot, atomic upsert via indexer assignment) and
    ConcurrentQueue<MessageEnvelope> _eventQueue (MPSC FIFO drain on
    Flush). A ConcurrentDictionary<string, int> _eventQueueDepthByTopic
    tracks per-topic residual event depth for the warning-threshold
    crossing check. Public API:
        - Enqueue(MessageEnvelope) — call site is any worker thread.
            * State kind  → upserts into _stateSlots (latest wins).
            * Event kind  → enqueues into _eventQueue, increments per-topic
              depth atomically; emits a single warning log the moment the
              new depth crosses options.EventQueueWarningThresholdPerTopic
              (default 1000). Subsequent enqueues past the threshold do
              not spam log; the warning re-fires only after the queue
              drains back at-or-below the threshold and is crossed again.
              Messages are never dropped (Req 9.5).
            * Request/Response  → dropped + warning log; correlation
              registry (task 2.3) is the dispatcher for these kinds.
            * null Topic  → dropped + warning.
        - Flush() — main-thread-only contract. Snapshots state slots by
          iterating Keys and calling TryRemove for each, then drains the
          event queue with TryDequeue, then invokes handlers via the
          IDispatchHandlerLookup. Each handler invocation is wrapped in
          try/catch; thrown exceptions are routed to the logError
          callback as a CoreIpcError.HandlerException message and
          dispatch continues to the next handler / next envelope
          (Req 9.2 / Req 1.4).
        - SetHandlerLookup(IDispatchHandlerLookup?) — late-binding wire
          for the upcoming TopicSubscriptionRegistry (task 2.4).
        - StateSlotCount / EventQueueCount — observable counters used by
          tests and the future IConnectionDiagnostics implementation.
    Constructor accepts CoreIpcOptions (rejects null and negative
    thresholds) plus optional logWarning / logError callbacks
    (Action<string> / Action<string, Exception>) so the queue can be
    unit-tested without a live CoreIpcLogger.
