Implementation summary:
- Lives in namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Dispatch inside the
  existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. No asmdef change was
  required because Core already references the Abstractions package and
  System.Collections.Concurrent is available from the Unity BCL.
- The design.md sketch of using Channel<MessageEnvelope> was replaced by
  ConcurrentQueue<MessageEnvelope>: Unity 6's Mono runtime does not
  ship System.Threading.Channels in the unityaot/unityjit profiles
  (verified by globbing the Unity install), and ConcurrentQueue meets
  the only required semantics (MPSC enqueue + FIFO drain + thread-safe
  Count snapshot). Adding the NuGet System.Threading.Channels.dll as a
  plugin would have introduced a dependency that the rest of the queue
  does not need.
- Warning-on-threshold is implemented as an exact-cross check
  (newDepth == threshold + 1) rather than a stateful "warned-once"
  flag, so the queue does not need an extra ConcurrentDictionary just
  to dedup logs and the test for Req 9.5 can assert exactly one
  warning even when many enqueues happen past the threshold.
- Handler exceptions are wrapped into a CoreIpcError.HandlerException
  payload before being passed to the logError callback so the eventual
  CoreIpcLogger (task 5.3) and CoreIpcDiagnostics (task 5.4) wire the
  same shape that other adapters will produce.

